     <h2><a href="http://greshams-law.com/2011/07/09/another-week-or-two-of-resilient-risk-assets-followed-by-another-downturn/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Another Week or Two of Resilient &#8216;Risk Assets&#8217; followed by another Downturn?">Another Week or Two of Resilient &#8216;Risk Assets&#8217; followed by another Downturn?</a></h2>
     <div class="date">Jul 9, 2011</div>
      </div>
    <div class="clearer"></div>
    <p>An update of the daily treasury statement indicators for 9/7/11. If one were to take the lagged charts at face value, one would conclude that there could be another week or two of buoyancy in &#8216;risk assets&#8217; followed by another downturn.</p>
<p> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://greshams-law.com/2011/07/09/another-week-or-two-of-resilient-risk-assets-followed-by-another-downturn/#more-4616" class="more-link">continue reading &raquo;</a></p>
    <!-- end .entry -->
