    <div class="post" id="post-4570">
      <div class="title">
     <h2><a href="http://greshams-law.com/2011/07/07/the-political-tide-against-the-ratings-agencies/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to The Political Tide Against the Ratings Agencies">The Political Tide Against the Ratings Agencies</a></h2>
     <div class="date">Jul 7, 2011</div>
      </div>
    <div class="clearer"></div>
    <div class="sticky_post"><p>The bane of our pseudo-capitalistic system is the blatant double standard that is upheld with respect to prices. If the money prices of things go up, that&#8217;s ok, and the saint behind this wholesome circumstance is typically elevated to greatness. However, if the money prices of things go down, there&#8217;s <em>got</em> to be a bad guy somewhere — and boy does he get hanged, drawn and quartered in the town square.</p>
<p> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://greshams-law.com/2011/07/07/the-political-tide-against-the-ratings-agencies/#more-4570" class="more-link">continue reading &raquo;</a></p>
</div>
    <!-- end .entry -->
  <div class="postdata">
    by <a href="http://greshams-law.com/author/greshams-law-admin/" title="Posts by Thomas Gresham" rel="author">Thomas Gresham</a> | 
